beer.beer_description: With the silly season upon us we dipped into our bag of hoppy tricks. Our mates across the ditch at NZ Hops kindly provided us with a pile of NZ-101 hops to test courtesy of their Bract Brewing Programme. NZ-101 is an experimental and unreleased variety loaded with lime, mandarin, melon, and tropical notes that paired perfectly with a crisp malt base and punchy bitterness of a NZ Pils. It's one for the hops lovers.
